WEBVTT

00:06.506 --> 00:08.507
I don't care what Bart says,

00:08.734 --> 00:12.085
there's nothing crazy about
taking your cat for a walk.

00:12.238 --> 00:14.304
[speaking gibberish]

00:17.926 --> 00:19.685
Huh?

00:23.858 --> 00:25.149
[dog panting]

00:25.860 --> 00:26.933
[goat bleating]

00:27.086 --> 00:28.152
[gasps]

00:29.104 --> 00:31.605
-[dog barking]
-[bird squawking]

00:31.699 --> 00:34.033
Wow. What is this place?

00:34.260 --> 00:38.037
This park is a paradise
for emotional support animals

00:38.264 --> 00:40.539
and their caring human partners.

00:40.766 --> 00:42.708
Oh, that's lovely.

00:42.859 --> 00:44.117
Now get out!

00:44.211 --> 00:47.713
Your mangy cat can't be
in here if she's un-vested.

00:47.864 --> 00:51.124
Oh, but my kitty
is so empathetic.

00:51.218 --> 00:54.795
She's the most caring,
lovable, gentle,

00:54.963 --> 00:56.129
-sweet...
-[chicken squawks]

00:56.223 --> 00:58.465
[gasps] My anxiety chicken!

00:58.634 --> 01:00.208
-[Snowball II yowls]
-[chicken squawks]

01:00.302 --> 01:02.636
Somebody do something!

01:02.805 --> 01:05.122
I can't do things,
I'm an empath.

01:05.215 --> 01:06.807
I'm conflict-averse.

01:06.959 --> 01:08.550
Support me, Apples.

01:08.718 --> 01:10.194
Oh, boy.

01:11.480 --> 01:13.906
Well, it was peck-and-go
for a minute there,

01:13.982 --> 01:16.149
but Gwyneth Poultry
is gonna be all right.

01:16.302 --> 01:18.151
Here's your astronomical bill.

01:18.320 --> 01:20.137
Oh, they'll be covering it.

01:20.155 --> 01:23.140
$16,000?! For a chicken?

01:23.309 --> 01:26.418
I just ate a whole bucket
of them for 20 bucks.

01:26.570 --> 01:29.646
Prosthetic beak?
Cluck-lear implant?

01:29.665 --> 01:33.550
Bawk therapy? We don't
have the money for this.

01:35.579 --> 01:37.078
[squawks weakly]

01:37.098 --> 01:38.839
[squawks sadly]

01:38.991 --> 01:40.340
Hmm...

01:40.492 --> 01:43.176
They say all it takes
to financially ruin a family

01:43.329 --> 01:45.771
is one unexpected medical bill.

01:45.922 --> 01:47.272
Who knew ours would be
for jacking up

01:47.441 --> 01:49.441
some bougie-ass chicken?
[laughs]

01:49.668 --> 01:53.612
I am so sorry. You can sell
my Malibu Stacy Dream House.

01:53.763 --> 01:57.116
It's increased in value.
I just redid the kitchen.

01:57.343 --> 01:59.843
Relax. We're not gonna
sell your toys.

01:59.862 --> 02:01.620
The sax is where
the real money is.

02:01.771 --> 02:02.846
Homer.

02:02.865 --> 02:04.606
What? My upper-lower,
middle-lower,

02:04.625 --> 02:07.442
lower-class income
isn't gonna get us out of this.

02:07.461 --> 02:10.111
Hmm. In order to save
this family,

02:10.131 --> 02:12.873
I'm gonna have to do something
I've never done before,

02:12.967 --> 02:14.466
get a job.

02:14.693 --> 02:16.360
Oh, you've had tons of jobs:

02:16.378 --> 02:19.696
cop, realtor, gym owner,
erotic baker,

02:19.789 --> 02:21.122
weed sommelier.

02:21.142 --> 02:22.866
Those were for my own growth.

02:22.959 --> 02:25.702
This time, it's not personal.

02:25.795 --> 02:27.962
Ooh, this one sounds perfect.

02:27.982 --> 02:29.206
They're hiring cooks.

02:29.299 --> 02:31.892
Ooh, cooking.
That's one of the only things

02:31.986 --> 02:33.543
I don't doubt myself at.

02:33.637 --> 02:36.471
"Exciting work,
competitive salary,

02:36.490 --> 02:38.973
team players wanted
at GimmeChow."

02:38.993 --> 02:40.475
What's GimmeChow?

02:40.494 --> 02:42.052
It's a new food delivery app.

02:42.070 --> 02:43.570
The teachers have been using it
ever since

02:43.664 --> 02:46.907
Lunch Lady Dora was on
<i> Cafeteria Nightmares.</i>

02:47.075 --> 02:50.669
[groans] They're only hiring
for evening shifts.

02:50.896 --> 02:54.247
Evenings? That's when you
and the food make dinner happen.

02:54.400 --> 02:56.082
I don't know how
to make pork chops.

02:56.235 --> 02:58.735
Where do you kill the pigs?
In the sink?

02:58.904 --> 03:01.329
Come on, guys.
We can help Mom out

03:01.348 --> 03:03.089
and cook dinner as a family.

03:03.166 --> 03:04.683
Aw, geez, you know,
I probably would not...

03:04.910 --> 03:06.000
Yeah, I'd love to, but that's...

03:06.020 --> 03:08.645
Homie, we need this.

03:10.191 --> 03:14.676
Honey, of course
we're all happy to help.

03:14.695 --> 03:17.029
Look, I'm already cooking.

03:17.180 --> 03:19.740
This is how nachos are born.

03:23.429 --> 03:26.538
Mr. Largo? But you
already have a job.

03:26.690 --> 03:29.357
I teach music
in a public school, Marge.

03:29.451 --> 03:32.044
Do the math. I sure didn't.

03:32.271 --> 03:34.546
<i> Folks, I'm Finn Bon Id√©e.</i>

03:34.698 --> 03:38.625
<i> I am CEO and head mind-blower</i>
<i> here at GimmeChow,</i>

03:38.777 --> 03:42.203
<i> and I came up with a way</i>
<i>to disrupt restaurant delivery.</i>

03:42.223 --> 03:44.281
<i> By getting rid</i>
<i> of the restaurants.</i>

03:44.299 --> 03:46.541
<i> -[explosion]</i>
<i> -Introducing</i>

03:46.710 --> 03:48.301
<i> the GimmeChow ghost kitchen.</i>

03:48.454 --> 03:50.637
<i> 20 new delivery-only</i>
<i> dining concepts,</i>

03:50.789 --> 03:54.215
<i> operating out of</i>
<i> one central kitchen, ours.</i>

03:54.235 --> 03:56.902
<i> Together, me and you,</i>
<i> and your shift manager...</i>

03:57.129 --> 03:58.720
