I'm gonna make it.
One last order,

13:26.281 --> 13:27.889
but it's too big to throw.

13:28.040 --> 13:29.891
[tires screech]

13:30.118 --> 13:31.542
-Aah!
-[song ends]

13:31.620 --> 13:33.544
Oh, no. No!

13:33.622 --> 13:34.804
[buzzer blares]

13:34.973 --> 13:36.973
[ankle monitor voice]
<i> Delivery failed.</i>

13:37.067 --> 13:38.215
[door squeaks]

13:38.293 --> 13:45.882
Food's... [shrieks] here!

13:45.900 --> 13:49.068
We thought it was a hobo camp
with a stolen credit card.

13:49.162 --> 13:53.072
[gasps]
You haven't been cooking at all.

13:53.224 --> 13:54.891
-Sushi time!
-[Bart and Lisa gasp]

13:54.893 --> 13:58.077
Worst of all,
my family lied to me.

13:58.229 --> 13:59.912
[Gil]
<i> No, worst of all is</i>

14:00.065 --> 14:01.247
<i> you're fired with cause!</i>

14:01.399 --> 14:05.401
[Gil laughing maniacally]

14:05.494 --> 14:06.827
[grunts]

14:06.847 --> 14:08.771
If you're hungry,
we've got dinner.

14:08.773 --> 14:09.764
-[grunts]
-[whimpers]

14:14.544 --> 14:15.836
I am so hungry,

14:16.005 --> 14:17.763
and Mom's eating
all the empanadas

14:17.858 --> 14:19.248
with the wrong sauces.

14:19.342 --> 14:22.343
Not the<i> verde,</i> use the<i> roja.</i>
<i> Roja!</i>

14:22.362 --> 14:23.936
She wouldn't starve her family

14:24.089 --> 14:26.180
over one little act
of betrayal, would she?

14:26.199 --> 14:29.659
Let's go for the pot stickers,
real casual.

14:31.854 --> 14:33.596
-[growls loudly]
-[all cry out]

14:33.615 --> 14:36.040
No wonder this jug
hasn't been going up.

14:36.267 --> 14:38.525
You've been getting
delivery for weeks.

14:38.545 --> 14:40.027
Honey, we tried cooking,

14:40.046 --> 14:41.713
but do you have any idea
how hard it is

14:41.864 --> 14:44.549
to make dinner
every single night?

14:44.700 --> 14:46.609
[Marge growls]

14:46.628 --> 14:49.370
My own family betrayed me.

14:49.464 --> 14:51.614
You know what family
would never do that?

14:51.707 --> 14:57.437
My union family.

14:57.931 --> 14:59.171
[gasps]

14:59.190 --> 15:00.915
What are you all doing here?

15:01.008 --> 15:02.675
Aren't you supposed to be
at work?

15:02.769 --> 15:05.619
We were so manchego cheesed
about not getting paid

15:05.621 --> 15:08.105
our overtime that we decided
to go on strike.

15:08.199 --> 15:10.533
And we can't strike
without our leader.

15:10.760 --> 15:11.759
Oh.

15:11.778 --> 15:13.428
And guess what, Tube Dress?

15:13.521 --> 15:17.098
All the other delivery app
workers are striking with us.

15:17.116 --> 15:21.210
Every food delivery app
in Springfield is shut down.

15:21.362 --> 15:22.879
Yes!

15:23.030 --> 15:26.257
[Homer]
No!

15:30.947 --> 15:33.114
Stupid strike.
I didn't realize it,

15:33.132 --> 15:35.224
but I've gotten addicted
to GimmeChow.

15:35.301 --> 15:37.618
I haven't eaten
since this whole thing started.

15:37.712 --> 15:39.729
Why don't you get something
from the cafeteria?

15:39.956 --> 15:42.899
Food only tastes good when
someone brings it to me now.

15:43.050 --> 15:45.718
[alarm blaring]

15:45.812 --> 15:47.311
-[alarm stops]
-[Lenny] Whoa, geez.

15:47.480 --> 15:49.221
-Easy there, Homer.
-You could've fried

15:49.315 --> 15:51.649
every electronic device
in Springfield.

15:51.801 --> 15:55.352
Mmm, fried electronic device.

15:55.488 --> 15:57.638
Aw, that one
didn't even make sense.

15:57.732 --> 15:59.474
I'm losing it. I need to eat.

15:59.567 --> 16:01.400
I'd sign a deal
with the devil himself

16:01.419 --> 16:03.494
-to get my GimmeChow back.
-[phone rings]

16:03.588 --> 16:04.979
Hello?

16:05.072 --> 16:08.649
Yes, this is union rabble-rouser
Marge Simpson's husband.

16:08.743 --> 16:10.985
Tonight on "Dollars:
the GimmeChow Strike."

16:11.078 --> 16:14.338
Sweet for labor,
or bat for business? You decide.

16:14.432 --> 16:16.599
Zooming in from Springfield,
union capo,

16:16.751 --> 16:18.009
<i> Marge Simpson. Marge,</i>

16:18.161 --> 16:20.085
<i> I'm gonna be as impartial</i>
<i> as possible here.</i>

16:20.105 --> 16:23.922
<i> Why are you starving America</i>
<i> with your psychotic demands?</i>

16:23.942 --> 16:25.775
<i> We're not starving anyone.</i>

16:25.926 --> 16:28.002
<i> All we want is our fair share.</i>

16:28.021 --> 16:29.687
<i> Is that too much to ask?</i>

16:29.839 --> 16:31.263
<i> Yes. And here to tell us why</i>

16:31.399 --> 16:33.007
<i> is GimmeChow's</i>
<i> new brand ambassador,</i>

16:33.100 --> 16:34.933
<i> -Homer Simpson.</i>
-What?

16:35.028 --> 16:37.286
Hey, Cliff.
Big fan of your whole deal.

16:37.438 --> 16:39.622
<i>Homer, you're working for them?</i>

16:39.774 --> 16:41.182
<i> I sure am.</i>

16:41.275 --> 16:43.292
<i> I was honored when GimmeChow</i>
<i> offered to pay me</i>

16:43.444 --> 16:45.703
<i> in GimmeChow gift cards</i>
<i> to talk to America</i>

16:45.855 --> 16:49.615
<i> about... "how unions</i>
<i> get in the way of innovation."</i>

16:49.709 --> 16:52.710
<i> You're in a union</i>
<i> at the nuclear plant.</i>

16:52.862 --> 16:55.972
<i> And I haven't innovated</i>
<i> one thing over there.</i>

16:56.082 --> 16:57.532
Look, we're living
in the future.

16:57.550 --> 17:00.868
This little device
can get me anything I want.

17:00.887 --> 17:04.388
Songs, sneakers, anonymous
gay hook-ups, so I hear.

17:04.541 --> 17:06.816
Why shouldn't it
also bring me food?

17:06.967 --> 17:09.377
But at the cost of human misery?

17:09.395 --> 17:12.155
Misery is how
all the best stuff is made.

17:12.306 --> 17:15.066
Pyramids, railroads, the blues,

17:15.160 --> 17:17.568
those great soccer stadiums
in Qatar,

17:17.662 --> 17:19.812
all the things America loves.

17:19.906 --> 17:22.832
Why do you hate America,
Marge? Ow!

17:22.983 --> 17:25.168
-[grunting]
-Hey! Ow! Marge, stop.

17:25.319 --> 17:26.819
I encourage everyone

17:26.838 --> 17:28.396
<i> who respects workers' rights</i>

17:28.414 --> 17:30.339
<i> to join us on the picket line.</i>

17:30.491 --> 17:33.826
<i>When we stand together, we win.</i>

17:33.845 --> 17:36.012
‚ô™ ‚ô™

17:36.163 --> 17:38.756
Marge, your speech on TV worked.

17:38.850 --> 17:40.925
Looks like the whole town's
with us.

17:41.019 --> 17:43.352
[all]
Hey, hey, we get how you feel.

17:43.580 --> 17:45.596
Oh, that's so nice.

17:45.690 --> 17:48.249
[all]
Now get in the kitchen
and cook our meals.

17:48.342 --> 17:51.085
-What?
-Attention, union thugs.

17:51.104 --> 17:53.679
The eaters of Springfield
have had enough.

17:53.773 --> 17:55.923
You have awoken a lazy giant.

17:56.016 --> 17:59.760
You're just corporate shills
standing in the way of justice.

17:59.779 --> 18:01.562
Shut up, burger flippers.

18:01.564 --> 18:05.691
Just for that, I'm gonna spit in
your face instead of your food.

18:05.768 --> 18:09.587
[all yelling]

18:12.775 --> 18:14.458
Good news, everyone.

18:14.569 --> 18:16.611
I found a way to end the strike.

18:16.704 --> 18:17.995
[cheering]

18:18.147 --> 18:19.630
You're meeting our demands?

18:19.782 --> 18:21.874
No. I'm firing everyone.

18:22.009 --> 18:23.300
[others]
Aw...

18:23.394 --> 18:27.396
Because GimmeChow Ghost Kitchens
are now fully robotic.

18:27.548 --> 18:31.400
And food deliveries are back
with non-complaining drones.

18:31.628 --> 18:32.902
[cheering]

18:33.129 --> 18:35.404
-[drones whirring]
-Ah.

18:35.556 --> 18:38.407
[sighs] I guess the greed
of the most selfish

18:38.559 --> 18:41.318
will always squash any hope
of a decent life

18:41.471 --> 18:44.805
-for the rest of us.
-Oh, my guy.

18:44.824 --> 18:45.973
Great work, Homer.

18:46.066 --> 18:47.475
Really, I could not
have busted up

18:47.477 --> 18:48.734
this union without you.

18:48.903 --> 18:51.904
And stabbing your wife
in the back? [chuckling] Nice.

18:51.998 --> 18:54.148
Gee, when you say it like that,

18:54.167 --> 18:58.094
it sounds like I stabbed
my wife in the back.

18:59.005 --> 19:00.346
[drone whirring]

19:04.827 --> 19:07.328
Oh... I thought that fried food

19:07.421 --> 19:09.180
delivered by electronic devices

19:09.332 --> 19:11.015
would've been
my dream come true.

19:11.184 --> 19:13.334
[gasps] That's it.

19:14.337 --> 19:18.531
Fried electronic devices,
now it makes sense.

19:20.860 --> 19:22.359
[chuckles]

19:22.512 --> 19:23.661
[alarm blares]

19:26.791 --> 19:29.292
My work is done.

19:29.519 --> 19:32.128
[cheering]

19:33.523 --> 19:36.524
The malfunctioning drones
are dropping everything

19:36.542 --> 19:38.693
from apple pies
to zucchini fries,

19:38.786 --> 19:42.788
but nothing is tanking faster
than GimmeChow stock.

19:42.807 --> 19:44.957
Props, where the hell's my tank?

19:44.976 --> 19:47.292
I can't get disrupted.
I'm the disruptor.

19:47.312 --> 19:49.645
I'm the crusher of unions.

19:49.797 --> 19:51.372
I'm the... Oh! [screams]

19:51.465 --> 19:54.058
That's what I get for using
non-union prop guys.

19:54.210 --> 19:56.110
[Homer]
Marge!

19:57.897 --> 20:01.882
Homer, only you could make
a mess this big.

20:01.976 --> 20:04.068
I did it for you, honey.

20:04.162 --> 20:06.554
All the food in the world
means nothing to me

20:06.647 --> 20:10.041
if you're not there to keep me
from choking on it.

20:10.985 --> 20:13.127
[both moaning]

